Democratic Alliance National spokesperson Solly Malatsi says the party needs to reflect on it’s performance in the elections. The DA remains the official opposition in the National Assembly, however, it has been dethroned as the official opposition in some provinces. The party has also lost five seats in parliament going down to 84 from the 89 seats it previously held. Speaking on the SABC’s Morning Live, Malatsi says, “We need to reflect honestly about our performance in these elections and we recognise that there is a lot of work we need to do as an organisation in terms of engaging where we came short in these elections.” Watch the full interview…